&lt;p>With time we explore the world outside &lt;br>
With time we dive into the world inside &lt;br>
Outside means which is available to all &lt;br>
All who have senses of seeing, hearing, etc. &lt;br>
Can explore the outside.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Inside means which is not available to our senses &lt;br>
For example food, you can search outside but hunger is inside &lt;br>
The beauty you see outside but lust is inside &lt;br>
Music is outside but the ability to enjoy is inside &lt;br>
Money is outside but the ability to give &lt;br>
the direction and purpose of the money is inside&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>